OL,3,COne in four unpaid carers in Wales
OL,4,Clive in poverty, report finds
OL,6,FChris Kemp-Philp, from Newport, has
OL,7,Fbeen an unpaid carer for over 40
OL,8,Fyears. He says the report shows unpaid
OL,9,Fcarers, many of whom didn't choose to
OL,10,Ftake up the role, are having being
OL,11,Fpushed into poverty by the sacrifices
OL,12,Fthey make.
OL,14,FHe said: "When unpaid carers do so
OL,15,Fmuch for the people they provide care
OL,16,Fto, as well as helping relieve the
OL,17,Fstrain on local health and social care
OL,18,Fservices, it's hard to believe that
OL,19,Fwe're left behind with such little
OL,20,Fsupport and expected to just continue
OL,21,Fcaring."
